In order to complete our sketch of the pronunciation of Latin as seen in the comic writers, we must also touch upon a subject which is, however, one of the most diffi- cult points in Plautine criticism, viz. tlte hiatus. After the uncritical labours of Lingc, Ritschl was the first to give some distinct and positive rules with regard to the admission of hiatus in the metres of the comic Writers, in the leth chapter of his Prolegomena, though his views as given there were afterwards in many respects corrected and enlarged by himself.
